arch:property.oc:show_val: This is a wall of seven courses, which is laid with ashlars of varying sizes with a white gray mortar in between the blocks. This wall was constructed to support the piers above it.
Floors, Loci 23 in the east sector and Locus 24 in the west sector.
Middle Pier Wall of the West Cryptoporticus (Under the Piers)
Arch piers Loci 5-10, the Locus 4 north south arch springer wall and Locus 16 ledge, and probably Locus 20 the east wall of the east sector of the West Cryptoporticus.
Extending in the middle of the trench.
Locus 12 the stepped east west retaining wall.
The arch springers and voussoirs extending from the face of the wall.

Phase IV: Nabataean Grand Design: 1st c. BCE to CE 1st c. The full Lower Temenos is constructed, complete with additional subterranean channels and drains, the Hexagonal Pavement, the East and West Triple Colonnades and Cryptoportici, the East and West Exedrae and the Lower Temenos Retaining Wall. East west crosswall is built in the West Cryptoporticus ca. 20 m north of the West Exedra.
This wall extends under all six piers. As excavated it is 13.65 m in length-by-1.32 m of east west width.
Closing Elevation: In the east sector on the floor 893.845 m.
